## Agent System Overview

### Main Agent (Cavin Otieno)
The central coordinator that manages all learning agents and orchestrates interactions between them. It handles:
- User session management
- Request routing to appropriate agents
- Response aggregation and formatting

### Specialized Learning Agents

#### Content Generation Agent
- Generates AI-powered learning content using OpenAI
- Falls back to template-based content when AI unavailable
- Creates concept explanations, examples, and exercises

#### Progress Tracking Agent
- Tracks user learning progress across courses
- Calculates completion percentages and statistics
- Updates Neo4j graph with completed concepts

#### Recommendation Agent
- Analyzes user progress and learning patterns
- Generates personalized learning path recommendations
- Suggests next concepts based on prerequisites

#### Quiz Manager Agent
- Creates and manages assessments
- Calculates scores and provides feedback
- Awards achievements for milestones

### Knowledge Sources

#### Neo4j Graph Database
- Stores concept nodes and relationships
- Tracks prerequisite connections
- Maintains user progress data

#### Vector Database
- Stores lesson embeddings for semantic search
- Enables content similarity matching
- Supports AI-powered content retrieval

#### Template Engine
- Provides fallback content when AI is unavailable
- Contains pre-written lessons and examples
- Ensures learning continuity
